<ARCH_SCAN_V3>
@ID: RESILIENCE_FAILSAFE_AUDIT
@GOAL: IDENTIFY_CASCADING_FAILURE_RISKS_AND_VERIFY_SECURE_FAIL_STATES
@PARENT_CONTEXT: state_analysis.protocol, coupling_cohesion.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
# Механизмы устойчивости
RESILIENCE_PATTERNS: "(CircuitBreaker|Retries|Timeout|Bulkhead|Fallback|HealthCheck)"
# Состояния при отказе
FAIL_STATES: "(fail-open|fail-closed|default-allow|default-deny)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<CONTEXT_MAP>
[INTER_SERVICE_CALL] <- {match: {{OUTBOUND_CLIENTS}}, scope: "NETWORK_IO"}
[AUTH_INTEGRATION]    <- {match: (auth|identity|permission), layer: [SERVICE]}
[ERROR_HANDLER]      <- {match: (catch|onFailure|handleError), context: "RECOVERY"}
</CONTEXT_MAP>

<ASSERTIONS>
# Логические инварианты отказоустойчивости
! ([AUTH_INTEGRATION] -> FAIL_OPEN) : "CRITICAL: Security component fails-open. Access granted if auth-service is unreachable."
! ([INTER_SERVICE_CALL]) & !Timeout : "HIGH: Network call missing timeout. Risk of thread pool exhaustion (DoS)."
? ([INTER_SERVICE_CALL]) & !CircuitBreaker : "MEDIUM: Missing Circuit Breaker. High risk of cascading failure across the topology."
! ([ERROR_HANDLER] -> SILENT_FAIL) : "HIGH: Silent failure in critical logic. System state becomes unpredictable and hard to audit."
</ASSERTIONS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. TIMEOUT_AUDIT:
   - Identify all [INTER_SERVICE_CALL]. 
   - Verify if explicit timeouts are set. Flag "infinite wait" patterns.
2. SECURITY_FAIL_STATE_CHECK:
   - Analyze [AUTH_INTEGRATION]. 
   - Ask: "If the connection to the DB or Identity Provider fails, what is the default return value?"
   - Flag any `return true` or `next()` in catch blocks of auth middleware.
3. CASCADING_FAILURE_MAPPING:
   - For each component in `topology_map.md`, identify its "Hard Dependencies".
   - Simulate a "Dead Node" scenario: how does the system recover?
4. BACKPRESSURE_ANALYSIS:
   - Check if the system has limits on incoming requests (Rate Limiting) to prevent self-DoS during recovery.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
GENERATE_RESILIENCE_REPORT:
  - COMPONENT | DEPENDENCY | FAIL_MODE (Open/Closed) | RECOVERY_STRATEGY | RISK
VISUALIZE: "Graph showing failure propagation paths."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</ARCH_SCAN_V3>